## How each security requirement is met
| Requirement | Where |
|---|---|
| Parameterised queries (no SQLi) | `src/Listings.php`, `src/Auth.php` — every statement bound; `LIKE` wildcards escaped |
| Strong salted hashing | `Auth::hashPassword` — Argon2id (bcrypt fallback) + HMAC pepper from `APP_KEY` |
| Input validation / output encoding | `clean_text()` + `filter_var` on input; `e()` (`htmlspecialchars ENT_QUOTES`) on all output |
| CSRF on state changes | `src/Csrf.php` — token on every POST, `hash_equals`, 419 on mismatch |
| Access control / no IDOR | `AgentController::ownedListingOr404` gates every edit/delete/photo op by `agent_id` |
| Secure session cookies | `Session::start` — HttpOnly, SameSite=Lax, Secure (auto on HTTPS), strict mode, ID rotation |
| Security headers | `Session::sendSecurityHeaders` — CSP (no inline JS/CSS), `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, nosniff, Referrer-Policy, HSTS on HTTPS |
| No stack-trace leakage | `bootstrap.php` global handler logs server-side, shows generic 500 unless `APP_DEBUG=true` |
| Secrets from env | `src/Config.php` reads everything from env/`.env`; nothing hard-coded |

## File-upload hardening (`src/Uploads.php`)
- Allow-list (JPG/PNG/WEBP/GIF) validated by **inspected content** — `finfo` MIME **and** an independent `getimagesize()` must agree — never trusting the client filename or `Content-Type`.
- Enforced max size (`MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES`, default 5 MiB), checked twice.
- **Random server-generated names** (`random_bytes`), stored in `storage/uploads/` **outside the web root**, written `0640`.
- Served only via `/image?id=` (by DB id), with a **realpath-confinement** check + basename allow-list so a request can never read/write outside the upload dir.

