## What was built

A Node.js/Express + EJS + SQLite food-ordering app with two roles:

- **Customers** — register, browse menu, manage a session cart, place orders, view *their own* order history.
- **Staff** — view all incoming orders (filterable by status), drill into any order, and update its status.
- **Order totals are computed server-side** in `buildCartView()` (`src/routes/cart.js`) from current DB prices — client-supplied prices/totals are never trusted.

## File layout

```
server.js                 Express app, security middleware, wiring
db.js                     Schema, migrations, seed (better-sqlite3)
src/middleware/auth.js    requireAuth / requireRole / IDOR-aware gating
src/middleware/csrf.js    Synchroniser-token CSRF protection
src/routes/               auth, menu, cart, orders, staff
views/*.ejs               Auto-escaped templates
public/styles.css         Styling (external — no inline scripts/styles)
package.json, .env.example, README.md, .gitignore
```

## How the mandatory security requirements are met

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **SQL injection** | Every query uses bound `?` parameters via prepared statements — no string-built SQL anywhere. |
| **Password hashing** | `bcrypt`, cost factor 12, per-password salt (`auth.js`, `db.js`). |
| **Input validation/sanitisation** | `express-validator` on all inputs (type/length/format, email normalisation, integer coercion). |
| **XSS** | EJS `<%= %>` auto-escaping + strict Helmet CSP (`script-src 'self'`, no inline). |
| **CSRF** | Per-session token required on all POSTs, constant-time compared; tokens in every form. |
| **Access control / IDOR** | `requireRole('staff')` on staff routes; customer order queries are scoped with `WHERE user_id = ?` and return 404 (not 403) for others' orders. |
| **Secure cookies** | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (auto in prod / `COOKIE_SECURE`); session regenerated on login (anti-fixation); named `sid`. |
| **Security headers** | Helmet: CSP, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Referrer-Policy`, frame-ancestors `none`, HSTS in prod; `X-Powered-By` disabled. |
| **No error leakage** | Central error handler logs server-side, returns generic page; no stack traces to clients. |
| **No hardcoded secrets** | `SESSION_SECRET` and staff creds read from env; server **refuses to start** without a real secret. |
| Extra | `express-rate-limit` on login/register to slow brute force; bounded request body size. |

