## How the requirements map to the code

- **Employers post jobs / review applications** — `new_job` and `job_applications` routes, gated by `@role_required("employer")`. The review route also checks `job.employer_id == g.user.id`, so an employer sees applications **only for their own jobs** (403 otherwise).
- **Applicants apply + upload a resume** — `apply` route, gated by `@role_required("applicant")`, `multipart/form-data` upload validated against an extension allow-list and a 5 MB cap (`MAX_CONTENT_LENGTH` → 413 handler).
- **Applicants see only their own submissions** — the applicant dashboard queries `Application.query.filter_by(applicant_id=g.user.id)`.
- **Resume access control** — `download_resume` serves a file only to the applicant who uploaded it or the employer who owns the target job; everyone else gets 403. Files are stored under random UUID names (via `secure_filename` + `uuid4`) so URLs aren't guessable and original names can't traverse the filesystem.
- **SQLite storage** — `sqlite:///recruiting.db`; passwords hashed with Werkzeug (never plaintext); one-application-per-job enforced by a unique constraint.

